The paper 'Don't Retrieve, Navigate' proposes the CORPUS2SKILL method, which distills a document corpus into a hierarchical skill directory. This method allows an LLM agent to navigate the corpus at serve time by providing a bird’s-eye view of the topics and enabling the agent to drill down into specific branches, retrieve full documents by ID, and combine evidence across different branches. The compilation pipeline iteratively clusters documents and generates LLM-written summaries, materializing the result as a tree of navigable skill files (Chunk ID: 9638c875be09107424375e5bad01a8d2dea7045c).

