The RoPE-Perturbed Self-Distillation paper proposes a training regularizer that creates alternative "views" of each training sequence by perturbing its RoPE indices. This method involves shifting the RoPE indices for a contiguous span of tokens, effectively increasing the distance between different parts of the context. The model is then trained to produce consistent predictions across these perturbed and standard views using a KL-based self-distillation loss, which encourages reliance on semantic signals rather than positional dependencies (Chunk ID: d37e5fd4ab42679bd78bac57267bbdde7f25b345, b451a5dd5a83b1b5ff9f76aefb523ba50d019019).

