The Doc-V* paper proposes an OCR-free agentic framework called Doc-V*, which formulates multi-page Document Visual Question Answering (DocVQA) as a sequential evidence aggregation process. Doc-V* begins with a Global Thumbnail Overview and alternates between structured visual reasoning and document navigation actions, such as semantic retrieval and targeted page fetching, to actively aggregate evidence before answering questions. This method is designed to improve efficiency and accuracy in processing long, visually dense documents (Chunk IDs: be67a9479ae7bfd65824732be14fe0823561a451, b9c11b48d119c8686f3b60b5acd75487c06b8bc4, 5a8ea508fddaef06f9eb29426a31c5786a5baf33).

