The FRESCO paper introduces a novel benchmark called FRESCO (Factual Recency and Evolving Semantic Conflict) for evaluating re-rankers in Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). This benchmark assesses re-rankers in temporally dynamic contexts by pairing recency-seeking queries with historical Wikipedia revisions, testing their ability to prioritize factually recent evidence while maintaining semantic relevance. 

