DocSeeker proposes a two-stage training framework consisting of Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) and Evidence-aware Group Relative Policy Optimization (EviGRPO). In the first stage, SFT is performed on high-quality data generated through an efficient knowledge distillation strategy to inject the Analysis, Localization, and Reasoning (ALR) paradigm. The second stage employs EviGRPO, which jointly optimizes for both evidence localization and reasoning abilities, while the Evidence-Guided Resolution Allocation (EGRA) strategy is introduced to mitigate memory constraints during training on multi-page documents (Chunk ID: 43aca11b66970e3fcf76670a19c3cfe0538109e1, 9ab276eb58b77979366279d7eb5f839a10d3a670, 445dddd2164e9e6033892def2ddd3ec7730991a4).

