The active knowledge navigation framework proposed in the NaviRAG paper is called NaviRAG itself. It shifts from passive segment retrieval to active knowledge navigation by structuring knowledge documents into a hierarchical form, which preserves semantic relationships from broad topics to specific details. This framework allows a large language model (LLM) agent to actively navigate the records, identifying information gaps and retrieving relevant content from the most appropriate granularity level, thereby improving retrieval recall and answer performance compared to conventional retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) methods.

