The MultiDocFusion paper proposes a multimodal chunking pipeline that integrates four key components: (i) detection of document regions using vision-based document parsing (DP), (ii) text extraction from these regions via Optical Character Recognition (OCR), (iii) reconstruction of document structure into a hierarchical tree using a large language model-based document section hierarchical parsing (DSHP-LLM), and (iv) construction of hierarchical chunks through depth-first search (DFS)-based grouping. This approach enhances retrieval precision by 8-15% and improves answer accuracy by 2-3% compared to conventional methods, addressing the complexities of long industrial documents (Chunk IDs: fc3482e37b96cc751366dc2bcb3cab130e41b48f, 622c00a7a9965e59ed77707faf9d13884551d424, b568c2c7c0ef979bb0f120971004dfef686ea5cf).

