The Knowledge Graph RAG paper proposes the Agentic Knowledge Graph (AKG) framework, which incorporates Recursive Crawling as a solution for navigating complex enterprise document ecosystems. This approach enhances traditional retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems by utilizing deterministic graph traversal and modeling relationships with explicit edges like SUPERSEDES and REFERS_TO to resolve versioning and multi-hop dependency conflicts. The benchmark evaluation shows a 70% accuracy improvement over standard vector-based RAG systems, providing more precise answers for complex regulatory queries (Chunk ID: 638cefbc9c94b199fda6e8bb7f564b37fd0cedc4, Chunk ID: 8d93ff60dc7cbfee201a40671290dfc306f06703).

