The OKH-RAG paper proposes the Order-Aware Knowledge Hypergraph RAG (OKH-RAG) framework to model ordered knowledge. This framework treats order as a first-class structural property and represents knowledge as higher-order interactions within a hypergraph augmented with a precedence structure. It reformulates retrieval as sequence inference over hyperedges, allowing for the recovery of coherent interaction trajectories that reflect underlying reasoning processes, rather than merely selecting independent facts (Chunk ID: c97bcd5081dc214717465a7f9cb97998ff4e4f86, 36aa44df5a8a2c06ef801f91a675a756a34bafe4).

