The Context Kubernetes paper introduces an architecture for orchestrating enterprise knowledge in agentic AI systems, which includes six core abstractions, a YAML-based declarative manifest for knowledge-architecture-as-code, a reconciliation loop, and a three-tier agent permission model. This architecture aims to deliver the right knowledge to the right agent with appropriate permissions and freshness, drawing a structural analogy to the container orchestration problem solved by Kubernetes. The prototype implementation includes components such as a Context Router, Permission Engine, and audit log, and has been evaluated through eight experiments demonstrating its effectiveness in governance and safety (Chunk IDs: 8f70ff42dc9a7cbf11ed5542f2104359c403c2b9, 47faca77e9ff4253eeaf77cf0de2ace06a908447, 01ec5dc3cd40fbe20de05537678a9cfdee0b4dd4).

